We’re celebrating today in the best way I know how! 🍫🥜

It’s Fooduzzi’s birthday, it’s my birthday, and we’re making *deep breath, because this is a long one* Vegan Chocolate Cupcakes with Chocolate Peanut Butter Ganache Frosting! 

So good. So fluffy. So rich. So decadent. And surprisingly simple to make!

Full recipe is linked in my bio. 🍫❤️

I’m playing with sharing Taste Test Tuesdays as Reels (as well as in my Stories) this year! And for today’s #tastetesttuesday, we’re trying @froozeballsusa!

My friend @gretchruns likes to take these camping or on hikes! Totally stealing that idea since they’re small and easily portable. 😊

Yay or nay on the whole Taste Test Tuesday as Reels thing? I’m very much on the fence. Lemme know if you like watching them in this format!

Chocolate Hazelnut Frooze Balls
$1.99 @ Trader Joe’s
8/10!

It’s Taste Test Tuesday once again, and today we’re trying the Quinoa Grape Leaves (Dolmas) from @traderjoes. 😊

I love eating a big ol’ plate of Mediterranean snacky things like this for dinner, so I am a big fan. Still like TJ’s rice Dolmas better though — they’re herbier!

Have you given the quinoa version a try yet? Are they new or just new to me? Lol.

Quinoa Stuffed Dolmas
$2.99 @ Trader Joe’s
9/10!

This new recipe has been in the makings for years.

Truly. Years. And only because I love to say it out loud.

Buffalo Falafel Waffle ⬅️ Go ahead. Say it, and tell me you don’t smile while doing it. 😊

I also just really love buffalo’d stuff. I recently bought two giant bottles of red hot at Costco, and the dent I made in one in just a few weeks is… concerning.

But I really do love it. Especially in these easy, vegan, gluten free savory waffles! 

I’ve had them for lunch for the past three days, and to say I’m a fan is a understatement. Recipe is linked in my bio! ➡️ @fooduzzi

Everyone’s posting red and pink chocolate recipes, so allow me to break up your feed a bit with some green!

Is the week before Valentine’s Day (and… ahem… the Super Bowl) a strange time to post a salad recipe? 

Absolutely.

But it’s savory, zippy, slightly sweet, kinda tangy, and just really oh-so good.

Bookmark this recipe if you’re interested but not until after V-Day! Or find the full recipe in the link in my bio now. You do you. 🥒🥑

#valentinesdaysalad? #fooduzzi #vegansofig

I forgot to tell you I published a new recipe this week!

It just so happens to have pistachios in it. That’s a coincidence and a happy accident to help celebrate St. Paddy’s Day, I guess!

These cookies also have dates in them! For some chewy, caramely surprises in each bite.

Plus lots of dark chocolate and just a sprinkling of flaky salt at the end. 

Hubba hubba. Recipe’s linked in my bio. 🍀

#ad Pittsburgh friends!! 🖤💛 Do yourself a favor and get to @aslin.pgh in the Strip asap. 

Their beers are so fun and totally unique (last time I was there, I had a beer that tasted like a sour patch watermelon 🤤). And their newest core West Coast IPA, Clear Nights, is a new fave. It’s crisp and a lil fruity and not too strong. 🍻

It’s available on draft and in cans at the Strip District location in @sdterminal! Have you been yet? What did ya get?

#ad Tis the season for THE BEST candy in all the land: peanut. butter. eggs.

Can we all agree that peanut butter eggs are far superior to their peanut butter cup cousin?

There’s something about the shape, the softness of the coating, the proportion of filling to coating, and the texture of the filling in peanut butter eggs that just... I have zero control when I’m near them.

And today, I’m sharing THREE vegan spins on the good ol’ PB egg:

1. Classic!
2. Cookie Butter!
3. Almond Chocolate!

So easy, extremely quick, and only 4-6 ingredients needed between them all!

CLASSIC:
1/2 cup peanut butter
1 tablespoon each coconut oil and maple syrup
3 tablespoons @bobsredmill Almond Flour

COOKIE BUTTER:
1/2 cup cookie butter
pinch salt (to tame that sweetness)
1 tablespoon each coconut oil, maple syrup, and @bobsredmill Almond Flour

ALMOND CHOCOLATE:
1/2 cup almond butter
1 tablespoon each coconut oil and maple syrup
3 tablespoons @bobsredmill Almond Flour
1 tablespoon cocoa powder
2 tablespoons mini chocolate chips

And, of course, you’ll need some melted chocolate to coat! I just melted some chocolate chips with a bit of coconut oil.

Which flavor will you make? (I suggest all three, but you do you!)

P.S. if you need the full recipe, it’s linked in my bio!

I know. It’s silly to be obsessed with a grain bowl. It’s just a bunch of veggies, a grain, and some dressing.

But man do I look forward to it every day when I’m eating it for lunch during work. And I thank my lucky stars I was feeling motivated enough the Sunday before to make a big batch to feed me quick, nutritious, delicious lunches all week long.

Loads of veg, chickpeas for protein, a creamy vegan balsamic vinaigrette, and lots of chewy farro make up this stunner! 🤩 And it’s perf to prep and munch on all week long. I now pronounce you Meal Prep Queen/King.

This Meal Prep Farro Grain Salad recipe is linked in my bio! 🥗❤️

Swipe to build a Vegan Seitan Reuben! ➡️

We have roasty toasty rye, a deliciously tangy and oniony spread, a thiiiiiinly sliced homemade seitan situation, vegan cheese if you fancy, and lots of zesty sauerkraut, and it is all just very very delicious.

Recipe is linked in my bio! @fooduzzi ✌️❤️

7 years after I posted my very first vegan Girl Scout Cookie dupes –– Tagalongs and Do-Si-Dos –– we now have another.

And arguably… the best?

Chocolate peppermint… oh boy. I go crazy over chocolate peppermint goodies. It’s my go-to ice cream flavor, I love it in other desserts, and Thin Mints were my favorite Girl Scout Cookie back in my Girl Scouting days.

These Vegan One Bowl Thin Mints are crisp, perfectly pepperminty, and extremely simple and fun to make!

Treat yo self this beautiful Tuesday. ❤️🌱 The full recipe is linked in my bio!

My go-to taco recipe these days! This recipe is super simple to make, but it really packs a punch thanks to the crunchy slaw and spiced, stewed black beans. 😊 

Pro Tip: Put the slaw into your tortilla *first* for a wildly delicious and texture-filled vegan taco experience. We’ve all had soggy, soupy vegan tacos before, right? These are the antithesis of that. 😊

Recipe is linked in my bioooo! 🌮

Is it weird to eat a salad that is just toppings? Perhaps.

Should that stop you? No. Especially if you’ve fallen victim to the high hopes of working your way through a bag of lettuce in a week only to find it in a very different color in a deep, dark corner of your refrigerator the following week.

I definitely don’t know what that’s like. Definitely not.

Groceries are just too dang expensive right now to allow for that. At least in my opinion.

That’s why I’ve been making a version of this salad every day for lunch for about a month. It’s everything I love about a salad, and find that I’m eating MORE veggies this way because I’m not at the mercy of the lowly bag of lettuce anymore.

I am FREE. And you can be free too, my friend. 🥬 

The recipe for my new “Just the Toppings” Salad (if you need it) is linked in my bio!

I did something slightly crazy and put COOKIE BUTTER in my iced coffee. And made a vanilla oatmilk cold foam.

I’m typically a coffee purist, but man was this a fun little treat. I love dipping the cookies that are the base of cookie butter in coffee already, so combining them was a force to be reckoned with.

So good, surprisingly simple, and just a little too easy to drink, you know? ☕️

Full recipe is in my bio!

I eat oatmeal every morning. And I never get tired of it. AND it keeps me full until (at least) lunchtime. 

I add 4 “Oatmeal Boosters” to my oats to make them so much more filling, nutritious, and, of course, tasty! Here’s how I make my perfect bowl of oatmeal:

>> Start out with 1/2 cup @bobsredmill Organic Rolled Oats (my fave, always). I’m partnering with them on this post!

😋 BOOSTER 1: Flavor
— You can use anything you want, but I typically use cinnamon and salt (and maybe some maple syrup if I’m feeling it!). A splash of vanilla is great too. In the fall, something like pumpkin pie spice would be fab!

💪 BOOSTER 2: Protein
— I’ve been using (and loving) @bobsredmill’s almond protein powder. The only ingredient is almonds, so it adds a nice sweet-nuttiness to the final bowl. Plus it makes the oatmeal super filling! I use about 1/4 cup for 10 grams of plant-based protein. If you don’t have protein powder (or if you don’t like it), try something like hemp hearts, chia seeds, or flax seeds. 

>> Add 1 and 1/3 cups of water and cook over medium heat until boiling, thick, and creamy. Add more liquid if desired.

🫐 BOOSTER 3: Fruit
— For sweetness and flavor! I’ve been using frozen blueberries because I like how they cool the bowl down a bit *and* how they get soft and jammy. That said, I always add them after the oatmeal is completely cooked so that they don’t get too soggy. Sliced banana, apple, and pear are some of my faves too.

>> Pour your oatmeal into a bowl.

🥜 BOOSTER 4: Fat
— For extra fillingness, I like to add some nut butter. I use peanut butter, and I’ll use anywhere from 1-2 tablespoons right on top of the finished oatmeal. Feel free to stir it in. Of course, use your favorite nut/seed butter –– almond, cashew, sunflower, etc. 

And that is my favorite vegan bowl of oatmeal (aka what I eat each and every morning). Each bowl has roughly 22 grams of plant-based protein to keep me full through the AM.

How do you jazz up your oatmeal? What are your favorite boosters?

The quintessential summer sandwich… made vegan!

Just because you don’t eat meat / are vegan doesn’t mean you can’t enjoy a BLT this summer.

And yes, I guess by definition, you can’t enjoy a traditional BLT because the B in a BLT stands for bacon and bacon is decidedly not vegan.

But if we rethink our definition of bacon… stick with me… then just maybe we can BLT just like our omnivore friends.

Today, we are entering the world of coconut bacon.

Stay! I promise it’s good. In fact, it’s SO good. I’ve been using the leftovers all week on… everything.

Coconut bacon is kind of crazy because the texture is just… very bacony. It’s crisp, kind of chewy, nice and fatty, and actually really flavorful (think: salty, smoky, and sweet) if you do it right.

And you know we like to do it right here at Fooduzzi. 😏

Recipe is linked in my bio!

This Vegan S’mores Bark might be the best thing to come out of my kitchen in a very long time.

And I mean, it makes sense. All of the ingredients scream nostalgia and summer, and you can make it in the comfort of your very own kitchen in like… five minutes.

Plus they are completely and totally non-put-downable.

I love a s’more. Rich and creamy chocolate + cinnamony graham crackers + ooey, gooey marshmallows = one happy and delicious little treat.

So today we’re taking all of those elements and… rearranging them? And making it a kitchen-friendly, fire-less recipe instead.

Melt, stir, freeze. Those three steps are the only things standing between you and indoor s’more bliss!

The full vegan recipe is linked in my bio! 🍫

Oh hey! New recipe time, and it’s for a luscious blueberry crumble… made entirely on your stovetop. 🫶

I hate (like… HATE) turning in my oven in the summer. And that’s because I hate being hot. Air conditioning is my favorite piece of technology, so if I can avoid turning my oven on and making my house even hotter during the spicy months of summer, I do.

That’s why I’m so thrilled with this blueberry crumble recipe. It’s so quick and easy because:

1. We make the filling on the stove in just 10 minutes
2. Our crumble is just granola! 

Granola gives this crumble that perfect textural balance and crispness without needing to bake it on top of the actual filling.

I partnered with my Best Foodie Friends, @bobsredmill on this recipe because their Lemon Blueberry Homestyle Granola is… I kid you not… my FAVORITE store-bought granola of all-time. ☀️

Full recipe is linked in my bio! @fooduzzi 🫐

Let’s make just FOUR vegan chocolate chip cookies because we 👏 deserve 👏 it 👏 (but we don’t want a big ol’ batch of cookies laying around for 2 weeks).

I created this recipe out of necessity. I needed a chocolate chip cookie, and I needed it stat.

So I made just enough for me to enjoy throughout the week, and oh boy was it a good decision.

No hard-to-find ingredients, ready in 30 minutes, and honestly truly probably my favorite cookie recipe to date.

Don’t miss out on these, friend. 🍪 Recipe is linked in my bio! ➡️ @fooduzzi

It may not look like much, but this is the End of Summer Sandwich of my DREAMS. 

I can’t get over how delightful, fresh, and zippy this combo is.

- Crusty Sourdough
- Dairy Free @boursincheese 
- Heirloom Tomatoes
- Dill Pickles

Everything sliced / spread super thin for a crispy, balanced party in your mouth hole. 

I can’t stop, nor will I stop. 🤌

Full recipe is linked in my bio! @fooduzzi

Can’t cry because I’m laughing too hard. What a mess.

Make sure your towel is DRY. 

Recipe at the link in my bio (and yes I still ate these).

Is there anything more comforting than a big ol’ bowl of pasta?

My answer: no. It is the quintessential cozy food for me, and I will praise its perfection all year long.

But… there’s something about pasta just hitting different in the fall and winter months. It is extra cozy, extra soothing, extra satisfying.

That’s why, when September started, I woke up craving pasta. And not just any pasta: vodka sauce.

Vegan Vodka Sauce to be precise! It’s new on the blog and oooooh so good.

Find the full recipe in the link in my bio or at fooduzzi.com!

We’re going a little wild today and making our own pasta. It’s one of those culinary things that makes you feel like a full-blown chef.

It’s something you can buy pretty much anywhere, but making it from scratch just seems so… fancy. Such a fun way to turn a regular ol’ pasta dish into one that’s really something to talk about.

#ad That’s why I was so excited @bobsredmill launched their 00 Flour this year! 00 Flour is milled extra fine, meaning any dough made with the stuff is extra elastic and tender. It’s perfect for homemade pizza or pasta!

Pasta making has been a bit of a love language in my family over these past few years, so the whole process of whisking, kneading, rolling, filling, cutting, boiling, and devouring makes me all warm and cozy on the inside.

And I’m excited to share that feeling (and this recipe for these fab Vegan Ricotta Ravioli) with you today!

Fullllll recipe is linked in my bio! → @fooduzzi

FALL FOOD IS THE BEST FOOD. I will scream this truth from every rooftop because I feel it so deeply in my soul.

#ad Maple is one of my favorite fall flavors, and I especially love it in @bobsredmill’s Maple Sea Salt Granola. It’s just sweet enough and has a nice salty bite. Kind of like salted caramel, just mapley instead.

To soak up my love of maple during this fabulous season, I challenged myself to use this granola in two different recipes. They’re fun, simple, and perfectly fit for fall.

We have Maple-Roasted Sweet Potatoes, piled high with the granola for a nice crunchy contrast. And dare I say: a fab Thanksgiving side!

And then we have a cute little, swirly parfait that I’ve been eating, no joke, for three weeks straight.

Snag a bag of this granola for truly endless possibilities this season! Use it as croutons on a salad, in cookies, or as a perfect little bowl of night cereal with some milk. ❤️

Both recipes are linked in my bio!

Have you ever made cinnamon ornaments before? We had them for our tree when I was younger, and I always looked forward to opening the bag they were kept in because they smelled so delicious.

And they smelled that way for 20ish years. Every year, without fail, the sweet, spicy cinnamon aroma would perfume our Christmas tree and make the holiday vibes that much more cozy and festive.

My mom and I decided to make new cinnamon ornaments last year, and we had a ton of fun making and decorating them. The decorated ornaments you see in this post are from last year, and yes… they smell just as cinnamony as they did when we made them almost a full 365 days ago.

We definitely learned a lot from our adventures in cinnamon ornament-making last year, so I decided to document them for you today!

Full non-edible recipe is on the blog today! Check it at the link in my bio 🎄

Hbd, Fooduzzi! 🥳❤️
